The paper focuses on developing machine learning models for micro-level churn prediction and link analysis algorithms for macro-level churn ranking in the context of mobile games. This involves techniques such as deep neural networks, edge embedding, attributed random walk, and link analysis algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
